  "text": "However, a question that remains unsolved is whether vascular endothelial dysfunction is the same in mother and offspring in preeclamptic pregnancies. An excellent study by Yu et al. [CITATION_1] found that offspring born after hypertensive pregnancy had a~2-fold greater reduction of total vessel density in the skin. Interestingly, this phenomenon was associated with reduced in vitro vasculogenic capacity of the human umbilical vein endothelial cells of the infant at birth and was proportional to levels of antiangiogenic factors in the maternal circulation.",
